title: Advanced Fitness System
description:
Efficient 4-day training split targeting each major muscle group twice per week.

This 14-week upper/lower split features 4 weekly sessions (2 upper body and 2 lower body), perfect for Novice, Beginner, Intermediate lifters focusing on General Fitness.

Exercise selection focuses on fundamental movement patterns that develop overall fitness, with a balanced approach to strength and conditioning. 

Program features include progressive overload mechanisms.

Weekly Schedule:
Monday: Upper Body
Tuesday: Lower Body
Thursday: Upper Body
Friday: Lower Body
exercise_guidance:
## Exercise Guidance

### Volume Guidelines
- Sets per exercise: 3-5
- Repetition range: 6-12
- Rest between sets: 90-150 seconds

### Recommended Exercises
#### Upper Body Day
**Compound Movements:**
- Barbell Bench Press (Chest)
- Cable Rows (Back)

**Isolation Movements:**
- Cable Flyes (Chest)
- Chest-Supported Rows (Back)
- Cable Lateral Raises (Shoulders)
- Overhead Press (Shoulders)
- Dips (Arms)
- Skull Crushers (Arms)

#### Lower Body Day
**Compound Movements:**
- Barbell Squats
- Leg Extensions

**Isolation Movements:**
- Hack Squats
- Seated Calf Raises
- Decline Sit-Ups (Core)
- Hanging Leg Raises (Core)

### Progression Guidelines
- Use double progression: first increase reps, then increase weight
- Consider periodized approaches to break through plateaus
- Implement deload weeks every 4-6 weeks to manage fatigue

exercise_guidance:
## Exercise Guidance

### Volume Guidelines
- Sets per exercise: 4-6
- Repetition range: 1-5
- Rest between sets: 120-180 seconds

### Intensity Guidelines
- Main compound lifts: 80-95% of 1RM
- Focus on progressive overload by increasing weight or reps each week

#### Upper Body Day
**Compound Movements:**
- Incline Dumbbell Press (Chest)
- Pendlay Rows (Back)

**Isolation Movements:**
- Floor Press (Chest)
- Pull-Ups (Back)
- Upright Rows (Shoulders)
- Z-Press (Shoulders)
- Hammer Curls (Arms)
- Skull Crushers (Arms)

#### Lower Body Day
**Compound Movements:**
- Lunges
- Barbell Squats

**Isolation Movements:**
- Goblet Squats
- Good Mornings
- GHD Sit-Ups (Core)
- Weighted Russian Twists (Core)

### Progression Guidelines
- Utilize periodization with varied intensity and volume
- Consider implementing RPE (Rate of Perceived Exertion) for autoregulation
- Plan deload weeks strategically to maximize recovery
- Consider specialized techniques like drop sets, rest-pause, or mechanical drop sets

Science-based program alternating between strength and volume for optimal results.

This 15-week PHUL program combines strength and hypertrophy training over 4 weekly sessions, with 2 power days followed by 2 hypertrophy days. Suitable for Intermediate trainees looking to improve Weight Loss.

Exercise selection focuses on efficient compound movements arranged for optimal caloric expenditure, while preserving muscle mass during fat loss. 

Program features include strategic deloads, autoregulation guidelines.

Weekly Schedule:
Monday: Upper Power
Tuesday: Lower Power
Thursday: Upper Hypertrophy
Friday: Lower Hypertrophy
exercise_guidance:
## Exercise Guidance

### Volume Guidelines
- Sets per exercise: 3-5
- Repetition range: 6-12
- Rest between sets: 90-150 seconds

### Recommended Exercises
#### Upper Body Day
**Compound Movements:**
- Dumbbell Bench Press (Chest)
- Inverted Rows (Back)

**Isolation Movements:**
- Landmine Press (Chest)
- Resistance Band Pulldowns (Back)
- Overhead Press (Shoulders)
- Push Press (Shoulders)
- Skull Crushers (Arms)
- Tricep Kickbacks (Arms)

#### Lower Body Day
**Compound Movements:**
- Barbell Squats
- Standing Calf Raises

**Isolation Movements:**
- Romanian Deadlifts
- Lunges
- Side Planks (Core)
- Weighted Russian Twists (Core)

### Progression Guidelines
- Use double progression: first increase reps, then increase weight
- Consider periodized approaches to break through plateaus
- Implement deload weeks every 4-6 weeks to manage fatigue

Traditional bodybuilding split focusing on one or two muscle groups per workout.

This 11-week body part split includes 6 training sessions weekly, each dedicated to specific muscle groups for maximum stimulation. Optimized for Novice lifters focusing on Strength.

Exercise selection focuses on key compound movements (squat, bench press, deadlift) with proper accessory work to build maximum strength and power. 

Program features include progressive overload mechanisms, rest-pause techniques, autoregulation guidelines.

Weekly Schedule:
Monday: Shoulders
Tuesday: Chest
Wednesday: Arms
Thursday: Legs
Friday: Rest
Saturday: Back
exercise_guidance:
## Exercise Guidance

### Volume Guidelines
- Sets per exercise: 3-4
- Repetition range: 5-8
- Rest between sets: 90-120 seconds

### Intensity Guidelines
- Main compound lifts: 70-80% of 1RM
- Focus on progressive overload by increasing weight or reps each week

### Recommended Exercises
#### Recommended Exercises by Muscle Group
**Chest:**
- Incline Dumbbell Press
- Machine Chest Press
- Decline Bench Press

**Back:**
- Pull-Ups
- Lat Pulldowns
- Face Pulls

**Shoulders:**
- Seated Dumbbell Press
- Reverse Pec Deck
- Overhead Press

**Arms:**
- Tricep Pushdowns
- Hammer Curls
- Overhead Tricep Extensions

**Legs:**
- Hack Squats
- Barbell Squats
- Leg Extensions

**Core:**
- Decline Sit-Ups
- Ab Rollouts
- Hanging Windshield Wipers

### Progression Guidelines
- Implement progressive overload by adding weight, reps, or sets
- For main lifts, add 5-10 lbs when you can complete all prescribed reps
- For accessory lifts, add 2.5-5 lbs when you can complete upper rep range

exercise_guidance:
## Exercise Guidance

### Volume Guidelines
- Sets per exercise: 2-3
- Repetition range: 10-15
- Rest between sets: 60-90 seconds

### Intensity Guidelines
- Main compound lifts: 65-75% of 1RM
- Focus on progressive overload by increasing weight or reps each week

### Recommended Exercises
#### Full Body Day
**Compound Movements:**
- Overhead Press
- Deadlifts
- Bench Press
- Barbell Squats

**Isolation Movements:**
- Resistance Band Chest Press (Chest)
- Resistance Band Pulldowns (Back)
- Overhead Press (Shoulders)
- Step-Ups (Legs)
- Barbell Curls (Arms)
- Medicine Ball Slams (Core)

### Progression Guidelines
- Add weight when you can complete all sets at the upper rep range with good form
- Aim to increase weights by 2.5-5% every 1-2 weeks
- Focus on proper form and technique before adding weight

6-day training split targeting pushing muscles, pulling muscles, and legs on separate days.

This 15-week PPL program involves 6 weekly sessions (2 push, 2 pull, and 2 leg days), ideal for Intermediate trainees pursuing Bodyweight Fitness.

Exercise selection focuses on progressive bodyweight exercises that build functional strength and muscle, with minimal equipment requirements. 

Program features include progressive overload mechanisms, supersets for efficiency.

Weekly Schedule:
Monday: Push
Tuesday: Pull
Wednesday: Legs
Thursday: Push
Friday: Pull
Saturday: Legs
exercise_guidance:
## Exercise Guidance

### Volume Guidelines
- Sets per exercise: 3-5
- Repetition range: 6-12
- Rest between sets: 90-150 seconds

### Recommended Exercises
#### Push Day
**Compound Movements:**
- Diamond Push-Ups (Chest)
- Resistance Band Lateral Raises (Shoulders)

**Isolation Movements:**
- Decline Push-Ups (Chest)
- Resistance Band Chest Press (Chest)
- YTW Raises (Shoulders)
- Resistance Band Tricep Extensions (Triceps)
- Chair Dips (Triceps)

#### Pull Day
**Compound Movements:**
- Dolphin Kicks
- Resistance Band Pull-Aparts

**Isolation Movements:**
- Superman Holds (Back)
- Resistance Band Hammer Curls (Biceps)
- Isometric Curls (Biceps)

#### Legs Day
**Compound Movements:**
- Wall Sits
- Lunges

**Isolation Movements:**
- Step-Ups
- Bulgarian Split Squats
- Mountain Climbers (Core)
- Side Planks (Core)

### Progression Guidelines
- Use double progression: first increase reps, then increase weight
- Consider periodized approaches to break through plateaus
- Implement deload weeks every 4-6 weeks to manage fatigue

This 7-week Full Body with Specialization program includes 3 training sessions per week, structured to optimize gains for Novice individuals pursuing Powerlifting, Powerbuilding.

Wednesday: Training
Saturday: Training
Sunday: Training
exercise_guidance:
## Exercise Guidance

### Volume Guidelines
- Sets per exercise: 3-4
- Repetition range: 5-8
- Rest between sets: 90-120 seconds

### Intensity Guidelines
- Main compound lifts: 70-80% of 1RM
- Focus on progressive overload by increasing weight or reps each week

### Recommended Exercises
#### Full Body Day
**Compound Movements:**
- Deadlifts
- Barbell Squats
- Front Squats
- Pull-Ups

**Isolation Movements:**
- Incline Dumbbell Press (Chest)
- Barbell Deadlifts (Back)
- Upright Rows (Shoulders)
- Seated Calf Raises (Legs)
- Cable Curls (Arms)
- Cable Crunches (Core)

### Progression Guidelines
- Implement progressive overload by adding weight, reps, or sets
- For main lifts, add 5-10 lbs when you can complete all prescribed reps
- For accessory lifts, add 2.5-5 lbs when you can complete upper rep range
